SIMPLE: countryman
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Countryman
<hw>Coun"try*man</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧n"tr⟦icr⟧-m⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Countrymen</plw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧n)</pr>.</plu>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An inhabitant or native of a region.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One born in the same country with another; a
compatriot; -- used with a possessive pronoun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In perils of waters, in perils of robbers, in perils by mine own
<qex>countrymen</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>2 Cor. xi. 26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who dwells in the country, as distinguished from
a townsman or an inhabitant of a city; a rustic; a husbandman or
farmer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A simple <qex>countryman</qex> that brought her figs.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Country seat</ent>⟦br⟧
